{
  "stem": "15721.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] First of all, we had heard that there was such a thing as Dachau because that had been in the news somewhere.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I don't know that we had heard about Kristallnacht yet because there's an eight-hour difference and timing and so forth.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then sometimes, the news here was really not particularly keyed to events that pertained primarily to Jews.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I mean, don't let's forget the-- the atmosphere in the United States in the '20s and '30s was not really particularly Philo-Semitic.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "On the contrary.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Anti-Jewish feelings were the good tone here.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And there were quotas in universities-- Northwestern University, right here in Evanston-- had a quota of 3%, I believe it was, for the student body.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There were no Jewish professors with tenure in the '20s and early '30s.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The first Jewish professor given tenure in the American university was in the middle '30s.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I think it was Lionel Trilling at Columbia, if I remember right.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the atmosphere here was not exactly so radically different that if something happened to Jews in Germany, the newspapers would have headlines.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "At some time, maybe they did.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't really remember that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It's wonderful that memory can be very selective and the capacity to forget is as precious as the capacity to remember.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I've forgotten a lot.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "What did you do when you heard that your father was in Dachau?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it so happened that the then-president of Hebrew Union College, Professor Julian Morgenstern, was in attendance at the wedding.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I showed it to him because he was the most exalted official that I knew.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he called the chairman of the board of the Hebrew Union College, who happened to be a Senator Alfred Cohen.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
